# UnitTo – Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the values before running the project.

## Required

```bash
# The canonical public URL of your deployment (no trailing slash).
# Used for sitemap, canonical URLs, OG images, robots.txt, and structured data.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://unitto.com
```

## Optional – Analytics

```bash
# Google Analytics 4 Measurement ID (e.g. G-XXXXXXXXXX)
# Leave blank to disable GA.
# Analytics events are only fired AFTER the user has given cookie consent.
NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID=
```

## Optional – Error Monitoring

```bash
# Sentry DSN for runtime error reporting.
# Obtain from https://sentry.io → Settings → Projects → DSN.
SENTRY_DSN=

# Your Sentry organisation slug and project slug (for source-map uploads).
SENTRY_ORG=
SENTRY_PROJECT=
```

## Notes

- Never commit `.env.local` to version control (it is already in `.gitignore`).
- All `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` variables are exposed to the browser — do NOT put secrets there.
- Server-only secrets should use plain names (without the `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix).
